HEADWORD: Morbillous
<hw>Mor*bil"lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>morbilli</ets> measles, dim. of L. <ets>morbus</ets> disease: cf.
F. <ets>morbilleux</ets>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to the measles;
partaking of the nature of measels, or resembling the eruptions of that
disease; measly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Morbose</ent>⟦br⟧
